snippet: Crews in Northern California cleared storm drains and residents loaded up on sandbags Wednesday ahead of a powerful storm that was expected to pack hurricane-force wind capable of toppling trees and power lines.
abstract: Crews in Northern California clear storm drains and residents prepare sandbags as strong storm approaches with hurricane-force winds; heavy rain could cause flooding.
lead_paragraph: Crews in Northern California cleared storm drains and residents loaded up on sandbags Wednesday ahead of a powerful storm that was expected to pack hurricane-force wind capable of toppling trees and power lines.

headline.main: California: State Braces for Powerful Wind and Floods
headline.print_headline: California: State Is Preparing for Powerful Wind and Floods
